explanation: The problem can be solved by analyzing the number of possible states for each number of presses. For 0 presses, there is only one state (all bulbs off). For 1 press, there are four states (all bulbs off, all bulbs on, or any combination of on and off). For 2 presses, there are seven states (all bulbs off, all bulbs on, or any combination of on and off, with at least one bulb flipped). For 3 presses, there are eight states (all bulbs off, all bulbs on, or any combination of on and off, with at least one bulb flipped, and at least one bulb flipped twice).

